課程概述 Course Description
       傳統上，土木工程師對交通設施最關心的議題為設施的安全性與可靠度，然而近年來，以永續工程為導向之交通工程設計已逐漸受到各界的重視。然而，如何將永續的概念加入傳統的交通工程設計中至今還並不是十分清楚。因此本課程的目的在於介紹如何利用整合生命週期與生命成本分析（Integrated Life Cycle Cost and Life Cycle Assessment）來檢視材料與工法在環境與經濟上對交通系統之影響。介紹複合與再生回收材料用於鐵、公路建設中的評估及試驗方法。介紹完整的生命週期評估的方法與探討其在評估環境，科技，社會及經濟政策上對交通設施之應用。Traditionally, the foremost concern among transportation engineers has been the safety and reliability of major infrastructure components. However, the engineering community, along with society as a whole, is realizing the importance of sustainability-oriented infrastructure systems. Yet incorporating these concepts into the design procedure as a primary goal remains unclear to many engineers.  Thus the class is aimed to introduce a methodology (Integrated Life-Cycle Cost and Life Cycle Assessment) that can be used to evaluate the economic and environmental influence of the transportation infrastructure system when the new sustainable material and construction procedure are adopted. Study evaluation techniques for alternative (green) materials. Study environmental indicators associated with the green materials used.  By combing these tools, it allows for rigorous scientific assessment of sustainable infrastructure design through environmental, economic and social indicators.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The sustainable development is usually referred to the development that meets the needs of the present without compromising the ability of the future generations to meet their own needs. Traditionally, the foremost concern among transportation engineers has been the safety and reliability of major infrastructure components. Until recently, sustainability has not been included in most infrastructure systems on any level. However, the engineering community, along with society as a whole, is realizing the importance of sustainability-oriented infrastructure systems. Yet incorporating these concepts into the design procedure as a primary goal remains unclear to many engineers. Thus the class is aimed to provide a platform for future sustainable engineering of civil infrastructure systems linking the micronlength scale of material microstructural tailoring to the meter-length scale of structural design. Study evaluation techniques for alternative (green) materials. Study environmental indicators associated with the green materials used. By combing these tools, it allows for rigorous scientific assessment of sustainable infrastructure design through environmental, economic and social indicators.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction to Transportation Infrastructure2Sustainable Trends and Issues3Earth System4Five Capitals: Financial, Human, Natural, Produced and Social Capitals5Life Cycle Assessment for Environmental Impacts6Spring Break7Introduction EU policy, EPD, LCA, and LCSA (life cycle sustainable assessment)8LCA cases studies and practices9Life Cycle Cost Benefit/ Assessment10Social Factors: Community and Individual Behavior11Term Project Proposal12The Sustainability Quadrant13Project Pathway and Performance14Sustainable Rating System15Field Trip16Developing and Delivering Sustainable Projects17Final Project Presentation18Final Report 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


